Installation of Ruby on Rails


1. Install ruby and ruby-dev dependencies:

# aptitude install ruby
# aptitude install ruby-dev
$ ruby -v
ruby 2.3.3p222 (2016-11-21) [x86_64-linux-gnu]
$

NOTE: ruby-dev required by rails:
      $ gem install rails
      Building native extensions.  This could take a while...
      ERROR:  Error installing rails:
              ERROR: Failed to build gem native extension.

          current directory: /var/lib/gems/2.3.0/gems/nokogiri-1.8.2/ext/nokogiri
      /usr/bin/ruby2.3 -r ./siteconf20180131-835-re5ril.rb extconf.rb
      mkmf.rb can't find header files for ruby at /usr/lib/ruby/include/ruby.h


2. To install Rails, use the gem install command provided by RubyGems
$ gem install rails

$ type rails
rails is hashed (/usr/local/bin/rails)
$

$ rails --version
Rails 5.1.5
$

$ type rails
rails is hashed (/usr/local/bin/rails)
$

Looks good!


3. Install sqlite3 SQL database engine:
# aptitude install sqlite3
# aptitude install sqlite3-doc

$ sqlite3 --version
3.16.2 2017-01-06 16:32:41 a65a62893ca8319e89e48b8a38cf8a59c69a8209
$


